The now vs. our road to get here. ~ I always knew I wanted to be a mom. I remember talking to my guidance counselor during my senior year of high school, and she asked me where I saw myself in 5 years? In 10 years? I told her I hoped to be married by 25 and have my first kid before I turn 30. Why I set these arbitrary guidelines for myself, I don’t know. The marriage one happened to come to fruition, but not the baby. 
•
When Evan and I decided we were ready for kids, I thought “cool, a couple months and it’ll happen.” Well, a couple months turned into a couple years and then we found ourselves at a fertility clinic doing all sorts of tests trying to figure out if there was something we could “fix.” Nothing came back abnormal, and we were left with our doctor telling us we were one of her “unexplained infertility couples.” We started with IUIs. After three failed attempts to get pregnant, we moved onto IVF and were lucky enough to get pregnant with Baby B. 
•
Everyone’s journey is different. We had a lot of uncertainty, anxiety, and tears along the way, but all of that led us to the now — 34 weeks pregnant with our baby boy. And let me tell you little man, mom and dad can’t wait to meet you!
•
Photos: 1) Growing Baby B 2) Another negative pregnancy test 3) Building up our supplies to begin IVF 4) Leaving the fertility clinic after deciding to move forward with IVF 5) Daily blood draws 6) My wonderful cheery husband at our embryo transfer #ivfpregnancy

Work selfie and a little background no one asked for. 🤣 I used to think I wanted to own my own clothing store. While I still think that could be incredibly fun, retail is also incredibly hard.
•
After I graduated college, I worked for an independent knitwear designer, then moved to Anthropologie for nearly 4 years. After moving to Colorado, I had a complete job shift and worked briefly at an eye doctor’s office as an optician 👓 (not my forte!) Now, I am an estate planning and probate paralegal. I guess my point in sharing is simply to say, it can be fun to see where life leads you!
